task_score.transcript: As a as an ex IP student, I'm very familiar with the ID list. I also did the IG CSE syllabus and I found the Ivy syllabus is much more practical and much more focused on teaching student skills, critical thinking skills, problem solving skills, and higher order thinking. And for example that the assessed coursework in IB really helps students apply their knowledge in a really real life situation, having to think of an idea. Think of a problem. Analyzing mathematics and generate and generate conclusions and insights from them, that is a mathematical skill that not everyone, not not many others syllabi can offer. So that's the reason why I chose IDV, right? The reason why I chose teaching is, is, like I said with the teacher who really inspired me, made me want to start teaching.
